nonTicketedEvents.name: The Polar Silk Road
nonTicketedEvents.description: Discover the Arctic through the photography of Gregor Sailer and explore the existing, potential, and unexpected impact that warming temperatures will have in this once pristine region.

nonTicketedEvents.name: John James Audubon and his Birds of America
nonTicketedEvents.description: This free display of engravings from John James Audubon's The Birds of America reaffirms why it continues to inspire artists, bird experts and conservationists alike.

ticketedEvents.name: Natural History Museum - South Kensington Admission
ticketedEvents.description:
You are booking free general admission tickets for the Museum at South Kensington, London. There are separate ticketing systems for Member tickets and Corporate Supporter tickets. If you'd like to visit Tring in Hertfordshire, you can book a Tring general admission ticket.

Please check your chosen date carefully before confirming your booking. There is a maximum of six tickets per order. Please select a ticket for everyone in your group, including children of all ages.

Entry to the Museum remains free, but since we closed our doors we've been losing vital income. If you can, please consider donating to the Museum alongside your ticket. Donations will help us to continue welcoming visitors and inspiring the next generation of scientists. Please note that donations are non-refundable.

This unique sleepover teaches kids aged seven to eleven the chance to explore the Museum after dark, take part in the fun, educational activities and discover our T.rex hidden in the shadows of the Dinosaur Gallery.
